<title>UK: INTERVIEW - No big Reckitt takoever in sight.</title>
<headline>INTERVIEW - No big Reckitt takoever in sight.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>British-based household and personal products group Reckitt &amp; Colman Plc said its decision to pay shareholders 152 million stg in the form of a special dividend and share consolidation signalled that it did not have a major acquistion in view.</p>
<p>&quot;Obviously if there was something right now we would not have done this,&quot; chief executive Vernon Sankey said in a telephone interview with Reuters.</p>
<p>But he repeated the group's determination to be the world's number one in household products and said the group would go back to shareholders for funds if the right opportunity arose.</p>
</text>
